seminars, and thousands of visitors, it’s shaping up to be the East Coast’s comeback party.</p><p>We’re featured several of the handmade bike builders already, check out these stories for a sneak peek at what’s coming:</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/01/road-to-philly-bike-expo-2021-peter-olivetti-channels-his-ancestors/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Olivetti</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/27/tom-la-marche-breaks-and-makes-bikes-philly-bike-expo-interview/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tom La Marche</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/25/interview-zach-small-amigo-frameworks-pbe/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Amigo Frameworks</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/20/road-to-philly-bike-expo-2021-pierre-chastain-of-blaze-bicycles-builds-and-tests-in-moab/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Blaze Bicycles</a></li><li><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/18/casey-sussman-junkyard-cats-pbe/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Junkyard Cats</a></li></ul><p>With Abus, Handlebar Mustache, Kryptonite, Wahoo, Engin, Trek, Industry Nine, Wolf Tooth Components, OTSO, Ritchey, Silca, SRAM, and <em>tons</em> more small and large brands coming, there’ll be plenty to see.</p><p>They’re also hosting 23 seminars and six rides, plus a few special events (get the <a href=\"https://phillybikeexpo.com/seminar-demo-grid/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">complete schedule here</a>). Get tickets and more info on their website.</p><p><a href=\"https://phillybikeexpo.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>PhillyBikeExpo.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"540133d76cd4d0a2961526280e8550c1b4347e12f1212d9edddc147626ea535b","category":"Cycling"}